.TH $home 5
.XI $home - "Users `home' directory location"
.SH NAME
$home \- Users `home' directory location
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B $home
\fIdirectory\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
The file naming  convention  utilizes tilde  ('\fC~\fR') to identify the users
home directory (\fC$HOME\fR). When entering a file name:
.CS
~/xxx    -> $home/xxx
~yyy/xxx -> $home/../yyy/xxx
.CE    
On  most  systems  this  is  automatically  set  to the  environment  variable
"\s-1HOME\s0"  if it is defined or may be defined  explicitly  in the start-up
file. '\fC~\fR' may be used in the \fCme.emf\fR files but must be specified as
\'\fC~\fR'. It may be picked up in command files as \fB$home\fR.
.FH
